{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd532a2a-2a36-4148-a5c1-295d12c49d3d","content":"No `SettingsPage.xaml` found in the workspace. Here's how to convert it:\n\n## Add `x:DataType` to enable compiled bindings\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is adding `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `ContentPage` element. This tells the XAML compiler the expected type, so all `{Binding ...}` expressions are resolved at compile time.\n\n## Catching binding errors at build time\n\n1. **Enable XamlC** (on by default in .NET MAUI, but you can be explicit):\n   ```csharp\n   [assembly: XamlCompilation(XamlCompilationOptions.Compile)]\n   ```\n\n2. **Misspell a property** → you get a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- CS0117: 'SettingsViewModel' does not contain 'Thme' -->\n   <Label Text=\"{Binding Thme}\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Treat warnings as errors** in your `.csproj` for extra safety:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   - `XC0045` – binding path not found on the declared type  \n   - `XC0022` – no matching property/method\n\n## Notes\n\n- If a child element has a different `BindingContext`, apply a local `x:DataType` on that element.\n- To opt out for one binding (e.g., a relative source), use `x:DataType=\"\"` to disable compiled binding locally.\n- Compiled bindings also improve performance by avoiding reflection at runtime.\n\nWould you like me to create the file in this workspace with the converted XAML?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b14401ac-7d30-4798-9fd1-98eaeca7733f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty and there's no SettingsPage.xaml file. The user is asking me to help them convert their page to use compiled bindings. Since there's no existing file, I'll provide the guidance directly with example code showing how to add `x:DataType` and catch binding errors at build time.","outputTokens":676,"requestId":"A853:77FDA:6450C3:73FDAA:69FBE20E"},"id":"2ad32efa-f16a-4c35-8acd-5c257f3434b0","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:51:40.218Z","parentId":"5d1e651c-0e26-4b91-962c-72b0764e14da"}
